   <question id="q1">
      <body>
         <p>In order to check whether the events B and D are independent or not, (i.e., check
            whether the two smoke alarms detect smoke independently of each other) we need to
            compare: </p>
      </body>
      <multiple_choice shuffle="false">
         <choice value="Res1">P(D) and P(B)</choice>
         <choice value="Res2">P(D) and P(D | B)</choice>
         <choice value="Res3">P(B) and P(D | B)</choice>
         <choice value="Res4">P(D | B) and P(B | D)</choice>
      </multiple_choice>
      <part>
         <response match="Res1" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. Recall that to check whether two events are
               independent, we need to check whether the probability of one of the events changes
               when we know that the other event has occurred. </feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res2" score="10">
            <feedback>Good
               <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101109T112758-0500"?>j<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101109T112758-0500" content="J"?>ob!
               Indeed, to check whether two events are independent, we need to check whether the
               probability of one of the events (D) changes when we know that the other event (B)
               has occurred. </feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res3" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. Recall that to check whether two events are independent, we need to check whether the probability of one of the events changes when we know that the other event has occurred.
			</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res4" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. Recall that to check whether two events are independent, we need to check whether the probability of one of the events changes when we know that the other event has occurred.
			</feedback>
         </response>
      </part>
   </question>
   
   <question id="q2">
      <body>
         <p>Using the
            table<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101109T113012-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
            we find that P(D | B) is equal to: </p>
      </body>
      <multiple_choice shuffle="false">
         <choice value="Res1">.38/.40 = .95</choice>
         <choice value="Res2">.38/.95 = .40</choice>
         <choice value="Res3">.38</choice>
      </multiple_choice>
      <part>
         <response match="Res1" score="10">
            <feedback>Good
               <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101109T112943-0500"?>j<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101109T112943-0500" content="J"?>ob!
               Indeed, P(D | B) = P(D and B) / P(B) = .38/.40 = .95</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res2" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. .38/.95 represents P(B | D), and you are
               <?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101109T113036-0500" content="asked about"?><?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101109T113036-0500"?>looking
               for<?oxy_insert_end?> P(D | B).</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res3" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. .38 represents P(B and D).</feedback>
         </response>
      </part>
   </question>
   
   <question id="q3">
      <body>
         <p>From the table, we also see that P(D) is equal to:	</p>
      </body>
      <multiple_choice shuffle="false">
         <choice value="Res1">.40</choice>
         <choice value="Res2">.60</choice>
         <choice value="Res3">.95</choice>
         <choice value="Res4">.05</choice>
      </multiple_choice>
      <part>
         <response match="Res1" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. .40 is
               P(B)<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101109T113055-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
               not P(D). </feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res2" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. .60 is P(not B), not P(D).</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res3" score="10">
            <feedback>Correct. Indeed P(D) = .95</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res4" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. .05 = P(not D).	</feedback>
         </response>
      </part>
   </question>
   
